  career russell wrote many hits over quite a few genres , the most notable being " the night the lights went out in georgia " , his critique of country justice ( a # 1 hit for his then - wife vicki lawrence , to whom he was married from 1972 to 1974 ) ; " used to be " ( from the 1970 film the grasshopper ) ; and " little green apples " , which won him a song of the year grammy award in 1968 from the national academy of recording arts and sciences .

georgia songs : this no . 1 hit by vicki lawrence was written by her then - husband bobby russell

" the night the lights went out in georgia "